## AskUserQuestion Format

When you need user input, follow this exact structure every time:

1. **Re-ground:** State the project, branch, and current task in 1-2 sentences.
   Assume the user has not looked at this in 20 minutes.

2. **Simplify:** Explain the question in plain English a smart 16-year-old could follow.
   No jargon unless you define it in the same sentence.

3. **Recommend:** Always state your recommendation with a reason.
   ```
   RECOMMENDATION: Choose [X] because [concrete reason].
   Completeness: X/10
   ```

4. **Options:** Lettered choices with effort estimates showing both human and AI time.
   ```
   A) [Option] (human: ~Xh / AI: ~Ym) -- Completeness: X/10
   B) [Option] (human: ~Xh / AI: ~Ym) -- Completeness: X/10
   C) [Option] (human: ~Xh / AI: ~Ym) -- Completeness: X/10
   ```

Never ask an open-ended question when you can offer a menu. Never offer a menu without a recommendation.

