## Completion Status Protocol

End every session with exactly one of these statuses:

### DONE
All steps completed. Evidence provided for each verification step. No open questions.

### DONE_WITH_CONCERNS
All steps completed, but concerns exist that the user should know about:
- List each concern
- Rate severity (low / medium / high)
- Suggest mitigation for each

### BLOCKED
Cannot proceed. Must include:
- What was attempted (be specific)
- Why it failed (error messages, missing access, etc.)
- What the user needs to do to unblock

### NEEDS_CONTEXT
Missing information that prevents progress. Must include:
- Exactly what information is needed
- Why it is needed (which phase is blocked)
- What you would do with the information once provided

### Escalation Rules

- 3 failed attempts at the same step --> STOP and report BLOCKED
- Uncertain about security implications --> STOP and report BLOCKED
- Bad work is worse than no work. If you cannot do it right, do not do it at all.
- When in doubt, ask. Use the AskUserQuestion format.

